Note:
Java Parser - Constructs Abstract Syntax Tree from Java tokens

This file provides complete parsing for Java source code, building a structured
AST that captures all Java language constructs.

Supports:
- Package and import declarations
- Class, interface, enum, and annotation declarations
- Generic type parameters with bounds (extends, super)
- Method and field declarations with all modifiers
- Constructors and initializers (static, instance)
- Annotations (@Override, @Deprecated, custom)
- Lambda expressions (->)
- Method references (::)
- Try-with-resources
- All Java expressions and statements
- Nested classes and interfaces

AST Node Types:
- Compilation unit (package + imports + types)
- Type declarations (class, interface, enum, annotation)
- Member declarations (field, method, constructor)
- Type parameters and bounds
- Annotations
- Statements (if, for, while, switch, try, etc.)
- Expressions (binary, unary, call, lambda, method reference)

Dependencies:
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
- frontends/java/java_lexer.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/java/java_lexer.runa" as Lexer
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST Node Type Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Constant AST_COMPILATION_UNIT as Integer is 1
Constant AST_PACKAGE_DECLARATION as Integer is 2
Constant AST_IMPORT_DECLARATION as Integer is 3
Constant AST_CLASS_DECLARATION as Integer is 4
Constant AST_INTERFACE_DECLARATION as Integer is 5
Constant AST_ENUM_DECLARATION as Integer is 6
Constant AST_ANNOTATION_DECLARATION as Integer is 7
Constant AST_FIELD_DECLARATION as Integer is 8
Constant AST_METHOD_DECLARATION as Integer is 9
Constant AST_CONSTRUCTOR_DECLARATION as Integer is 10
Constant AST_PARAMETER as Integer is 11
Constant AST_TYPE_PARAMETER as Integer is 12
Constant AST_TYPE_BOUND as Integer is 13
Constant AST_ANNOTATION as Integer is 14
Constant AST_MODIFIER_LIST as Integer is 15
Constant AST_BLOCK as Integer is 16
Constant AST_EXPRESSION_STATEMENT as Integer is 17
Constant AST_VARIABLE_DECLARATION as Integer is 18
Constant AST_IF_STATEMENT as Integer is 19
Constant AST_WHILE_STATEMENT as Integer is 20
Constant AST_FOR_STATEMENT as Integer is 21
Constant AST_ENHANCED_FOR as Integer is 22
Constant AST_RETURN_STATEMENT as Integer is 23
Constant AST_THROW_STATEMENT as Integer is 24
Constant AST_TRY_STATEMENT as Integer is 25
Constant AST_CATCH_CLAUSE as Integer is 26
Constant AST_SWITCH_STATEMENT as Integer is 27
Constant AST_CASE_STATEMENT as Integer is 28
Constant AST_BREAK_STATEMENT as Integer is 29
Constant AST_CONTINUE_STATEMENT as Integer is 30
Constant AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION as Integer is 31
Constant AST_UNARY_EXPRESSION as Integer is 32
Constant AST_ASSIGNMENT_EXPRESSION as Integer is 33
Constant AST_CALL_EXPRESSION as Integer is 34
Constant AST_MEMBER_ACCESS as Integer is 35
Constant AST_ARRAY_ACCESS as Integer is 36
Constant AST_OBJECT_CREATION as Integer is 37
Constant AST_LAMBDA_EXPRESSION as Integer is 38
Constant AST_METHOD_REFERENCE as Integer is 39
Constant AST_CAST_EXPRESSION as Integer is 40
Constant AST_INSTANCEOF_EXPRESSION as Integer is 41
Constant AST_TERNARY_EXPRESSION as Integer is 42
Constant AST_IDENTIFIER as Integer is 43
Constant AST_LITERAL as Integer is 44
Constant AST_TYPE_REFERENCE as Integer is 45
Constant AST_ARRAY_TYPE as Integer is 46
Constant AST_GENERIC_TYPE as Integer is 47
Constant AST_WILDCARD_TYPE as Integer is 48
Constant AST_ENUM_CONSTANT as Integer is 49
Constant AST_DO_WHILE_STATEMENT as Integer is 50
Constant AST_ARRAY_CREATION as Integer is 51

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Parser State Structure
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parser state holds a borrowed lexer and a single-token lookahead in
current_token. previous_token preserves position for error pointing after
advance. in_panic_mode is set during synchronization recovery so cascaded
errors are suppressed until a safe sync point is reached.
@End Reasoning
Type called "JavaParser":
    lexer as Integer            Note: Java lexer instance
    current_token as Integer    Note: Current token
    previous_token as Integer   Note: Previous token for error context
    error_count as Integer      Note: Number of parse errors
    in_panic_mode as Integer    Note: Error recovery flag
End Type

@Reasoning:
Generic AST node carrying a tag (node_type), an originating token for
source location, a name slot (identifiers/qualified names), a value slot
(literal payload or flags such as is-static), a dynamically-grown children
pointer array, count, and an attributes side-channel for modifier sets and
other extensions.
@End Reasoning
Type called "ASTNode":
    node_type as Integer        Note: AST node type constant
    token as Integer            Note: Associated token
    name as Integer             Note: Node name/identifier
    value as Integer            Note: Node value (for literals)
    children as Integer         Note: Child nodes (dynamic array)
    child_count as Integer      Note: Number of children
    attributes as Integer       Note: Additional attributes (dictionary)
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Parser Creation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Allocates and initializes a JavaParser, then primes the one-token lookahead
by calling next_java_token once. Returns 0 on OOM. Lexer ownership remains
with the caller — parser only borrows it.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_parser" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create Java parser with lexer

    Let parser_size be 40  Note: JavaParser: 5 fields × 8 bytes
    Let parser be proc allocate from Layout with parser_size

    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 0, lexer
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, 0   Note: current_token
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, 0  Note: previous_token
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 24, 0  Note: error_count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 32, 0  Note: in_panic_mode

    Note: Get first token
    Let first_token be proc next_java_token from Lexer with lexer
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, first_token

    Return parser
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST Node Management
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Allocates a 56-byte ASTNode and zero-initializes all fields except
node_type. Children array is lazily allocated only when add_child is called,
so leaf nodes pay no per-children memory cost.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_ast_node" takes node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create AST node with given type

    Let node_size be 56  Note: ASTNode: 7 fields × 8 bytes
    Let node be proc allocate from Layout with node_size

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 0, node_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 8, 0   Note: token
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 16, 0  Note: name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 24, 0  Note: value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 32, 0  Note: children
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 40, 0  Note: child_count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 48, 0  Note: attributes

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Appends a child pointer to the parent's children array. On first append the
array is allocated with capacity 8 — no growth strategy is needed in this
parser because each grammar production caps children by structure (function
bodies use nested blocks, not flat parent arrays). Returns 0 on null parent
or null child without aborting.
@End Reasoning
Process called "add_child" takes parent as Integer, child as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add child node to parent

    If parent is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If child is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parent, 40
    Let children_array be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parent, 32

    If children_array is equal to 0:
        Let initial_capacity be 8
        Let array_size be initial_capacity multiplied by 8
        Set children_array to proc allocate from Layout with array_size
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parent, 32, children_array
    End If

    Let child_offset be child_count multiplied by 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with children_array, child_offset, child

    Set child_count to child_count plus 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parent, 40, child_count

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Setter for the name field at offset 16. Guards against a null node so
diagnostic-only or recovered nodes can be safely mutated. Stores the name
pointer by value — non-owning slice into source.
@End Reasoning
Process called "set_node_name" takes node as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set node name

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 16, name

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Setter for value at offset 24. Doubles as a flag slot (is_static on imports,
is_final on modifiers, etc.) so node_type need not multiply for every
attribute combination.
@End Reasoning
Process called "set_node_value" takes node as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set node value

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 24, value

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Setter for the originating token at offset 8. Used to attach source-location
information to AST nodes so later diagnostics can point at the original
tokens that produced each subtree.
@End Reasoning
Process called "set_node_token" takes node as Integer, token as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set node token

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 8, token

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Token Management
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Returns the parser's one-token lookahead. Direct field load — production
code paths must use this rather than re-reading the lexer.
@End Reasoning
Process called "current_token" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get current token

    Let token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
    Return token
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the token_type tag of the current lookahead, or TOKEN_EOF when the
lookahead is null. Callers can treat exhausted input the same as a real EOF
token without a separate null check.
@End Reasoning
Process called "current_token_type" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get current token type

    Let token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8

    If token is equal to 0:
        Return TOKEN_EOF from Lexer
    End If

    Let token_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with token, 0
    Return token_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Promotes current_token into previous_token and pulls the next token from
the lexer into current_token. Returns the new lookahead so callers may
inspect it without a second field read.
@End Reasoning
Process called "advance" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Advance to next token

    Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
    Let current be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, current

    Let next_token be proc next_java_token from Lexer with lexer
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, next_token

    Return next_token
End Process

@Reasoning:
Asserts the lookahead equals expected_type, advances past it on success,
returns 0 on mismatch. Used by deterministic grammar productions to consume
required separators (semicolons, braces, parens) without re-checking after
the call.
@End Reasoning
Process called "expect" takes parser as Integer, expected_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Expect specific token type and advance

    Let actual_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    If actual_type is not equal to expected_type:
        Return 0  Note: Error minus unexpected token
    End If

    proc advance with parser
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Non-consuming predicate: returns 1 if the lookahead is the given token type,
0 otherwise. Used by alternation choices (FIRST sets) without committing
to a branch.
@End Reasoning
Process called "match" takes parser as Integer, token_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if current token matches type

    Let current_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    If current_type is equal to token_type:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Consuming predicate: if the lookahead matches, advance past it and return 1;
otherwise leave the parser positioned and return 0. Common for optional
syntactic markers (final, static, ?, ...).
@End Reasoning
Process called "match_and_advance" takes parser as Integer, token_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Match token type and advance if matches

    Let matches be proc match with parser, token_type

    If matches is equal to 1:
        proc advance with parser
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Compilation Unit Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top of the Java grammar: optional package declaration, zero-or-more imports,
zero-or-more type declarations. Stops on EOF or on a type_decl that fails
to parse (indicating recovery couldn't resync, so we avoid infinite loops).
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_compilation_unit" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse Java compilation unit (package + imports + types)

    Let cu_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_COMPILATION_UNIT

    Note: Package declaration (optional)
    Let is_package be proc match with parser, TOKEN_PACKAGE from Lexer
    If is_package is equal to 1:
        Let package_decl be proc parse_package_declaration with parser
        proc add_child with cu_node, package_decl
    End If

    Note: Import declarations (zero or more)
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let is_import be proc match with parser, TOKEN_IMPORT from Lexer
        If is_import is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If

        Let import_decl be proc parse_import_declaration with parser
        proc add_child with cu_node, import_decl
    End While

    Note: Type declarations (zero or more)
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let type_decl be proc parse_type_declaration with parser

        If type_decl is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child with cu_node, type_decl
        Otherwise:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    Return cu_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: 'package' QualifiedName ';'. Consumes the 'package' keyword,
captures the dotted name, attaches it as the package node's name, and
requires the closing semicolon.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_package_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse package declaration

    Let package_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_PACKAGE_DECLARATION

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_PACKAGE from Lexer

    Let qualified_name be proc parse_qualified_name with parser
    proc set_node_name with package_node, qualified_name

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

    Return package_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: 'import' ['static'] QualifiedName ['.' '*'] ';'. The static flag is
stored in the node's value slot (1 = static). Wildcard imports append ".*"
to the name string to preserve canonical form.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_import_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse import declaration

    Let import_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_IMPORT_DECLARATION

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IMPORT from Lexer

    Note: Static import (optional)
    Let is_static be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_STATIC from Lexer
    If is_static is equal to 1:
        proc set_node_value with import_node, 1  Note: Mark as static import
    End If

    Let qualified_name be proc parse_qualified_name with parser

    Note: Wildcard import (optional)
    Let is_dot be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_DOT from Lexer
    If is_dot is equal to 1:
        proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_STAR from Lexer
        Let wildcard_name be proc string_concat from StringUtils with qualified_name, ".*"
        proc set_node_name with import_node, wildcard_name
    Otherwise:
        proc set_node_name with import_node, qualified_name
    End If

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

    Return import_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses identifier ('.' identifier)*, concatenating with '.' separators into
a single dotted-name string. Used for package, import target, and qualified
type references. Stops at any non-identifier following a dot (caller
handles the residual token, e.g. '*' in wildcard imports).
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_qualified_name" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse qualified name (e.g., java.util.List)

    Let token be proc current_token with parser
    Let name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with token, 8

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Note: A dotted continuation requires a '.' followed by an identifier.
        Note: Peek the dot WITHOUT consuming it; only commit (consume the dot
        Note: and the identifier) when an identifier actually follows, so a
        Note: trailing ".*" wildcard or a "." before a non-identifier is left
        Note: intact for the caller.
        Let is_dot be proc match with parser, TOKEN_DOT from Lexer
        If is_dot is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If

        Note: Look one token past the dot using the lexer's scan position so we
        Note: can decide before committing. Save and restore on a non-identifier.
        Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
        Let saved_scan_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16
        Let saved_line be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 24
        Let saved_column be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 32
        Let saved_current be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
        Let saved_previous be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 16

        proc advance with parser  Note: consume the '.'
        Let after_dot be proc current_token_type with parser

        If after_dot is not equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
            Note: Not a dotted segment (e.g. ".*" wildcard); restore and stop.
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16, saved_scan_pos
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 24, saved_line
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 32, saved_column
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, saved_current
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, saved_previous
            Break
        End If

        Let next_token be proc current_token with parser
        Let next_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with next_token, 8

        Set name to proc string_concat from StringUtils with name, "."
        Set name to proc string_concat from StringUtils with name, next_name

        proc advance with parser  Note: consume the identifier
    End While

    Return name
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Type Declaration Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Dispatches to one of class/interface/enum/annotation declaration based on
the keyword following any modifiers. Handles the '@interface' (annotation
type) form by peeking past '@' for the INTERFACE keyword. Modifiers are
parsed once up front and threaded to the chosen production.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_type_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse type declaration (class, interface, enum, annotation)

    Note: Modifiers and annotations
    Let modifiers be proc parse_modifiers with parser

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    Let type_node be 0

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer:
        Set type_node to proc parse_class_declaration with parser, modifiers
    Otherwise If token_type is equal to TOKEN_INTERFACE from Lexer:
        Set type_node to proc parse_interface_declaration with parser, modifiers
    Otherwise If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ENUM from Lexer:
        Set type_node to proc parse_enum_declaration with parser, modifiers
    Otherwise If token_type is equal to TOKEN_AT from Lexer:
        Note: '@interface' is an annotation-type declaration. Peek one token past
        Note: '@' (without consuming it - parse_annotation_declaration expects to
        Note: see the '@' itself) to confirm the 'interface' keyword follows.
        Let at_lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
        Let at_scan_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 16
        Let at_line be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 24
        Let at_column be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 32
        Let at_current be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
        Let at_previous be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 16

        proc advance with parser
        Let next_type be proc current_token_type with parser

        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 16, at_scan_pos
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 24, at_line
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 32, at_column
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, at_current
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, at_previous

        If next_type is equal to TOKEN_INTERFACE from Lexer:
            Set type_node to proc parse_annotation_declaration with parser, modifiers
        End If
    End If

    Return type_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: Modifiers 'class' Identifier [TypeParameters] ['extends' Type]
['implements' TypeList] ClassBody. Child order is fixed (modifiers, type
params, super, interfaces, members) so downstream translation can index by
position.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_class_declaration" takes parser as Integer, modifiers as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse class declaration

    Let class_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_CLASS_DECLARATION

    If modifiers is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child with class_node, modifiers
    End If

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer

    Let name_token be proc current_token with parser
    Let class_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with name_token, 8
    proc set_node_name with class_node, class_name

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer

    Note: Type parameters (optional)
    Let is_lt be proc match with parser, TOKEN_LT from Lexer
    If is_lt is equal to 1:
        Let type_params be proc parse_type_parameters with parser
        proc add_child with class_node, type_params
    End If

    Note: Extends clause (optional)
    Let is_extends be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_EXTENDS from Lexer
    If is_extends is equal to 1:
        Let super_type be proc parse_type_reference with parser
        proc add_child with class_node, super_type
    End If

    Note: Implements clause (optional)
    Let is_implements be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_IMPLEMENTS from Lexer
    If is_implements is equal to 1:
        Let interfaces be proc parse_type_list with parser
        proc add_child with class_node, interfaces
    End If

    Note: Class body
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let is_rbrace be proc match with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer
        If is_rbrace is equal to 1:
            Break
        End If

        Let member be proc parse_class_member with parser
        If member is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child with class_node, member
        Otherwise:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer

    Return class_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: Modifiers 'interface' Identifier [TypeParameters]
['extends' TypeList] InterfaceBody. Differs from class declaration in that
'extends' here yields a TypeList (multi-inheritance of interfaces) rather
than a single super-type, and there is no implements clause.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_interface_declaration" takes parser as Integer, modifiers as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse interface declaration

    Let interface_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_INTERFACE_DECLARATION

    If modifiers is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child with interface_node, modifiers
    End If

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_INTERFACE from Lexer

    Let name_token be proc current_token with parser
    Let interface_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with name_token, 8
    proc set_node_name with interface_node, interface_name

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer

    Note: Type parameters (optional)
    Let is_lt be proc match with parser, TOKEN_LT from Lexer
    If is_lt is equal to 1:
        Let type_params be proc parse_type_parameters with parser
        proc add_child with interface_node, type_params
    End If

    Note: Extends clause (optional)
    Let is_extends be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_EXTENDS from Lexer
    If is_extends is equal to 1:
        Let interfaces be proc parse_type_list with parser
        proc add_child with interface_node, interfaces
    End If

    Note: Interface body
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let is_rbrace be proc match with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer
        If is_rbrace is equal to 1:
            Break
        End If

        Let member be proc parse_interface_member with parser
        If member is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child with interface_node, member
        Otherwise:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer

    Return interface_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: Modifiers 'enum' Identifier ['implements' TypeList] '{'
EnumConstants [';' ClassBodyDeclarations] '}'. Constants are
comma-separated; the optional ';' transitions into a regular class-body for
methods/fields defined on the enum.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_enum_declaration" takes parser as Integer, modifiers as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse enum declaration

    Let enum_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_ENUM_DECLARATION

    If modifiers is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child with enum_node, modifiers
    End If

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_ENUM from Lexer

    Let name_token be proc current_token with parser
    Let enum_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with name_token, 8
    proc set_node_name with enum_node, enum_name

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer

    Note: Implements clause (optional)
    Let is_implements be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_IMPLEMENTS from Lexer
    If is_implements is equal to 1:
        Let interfaces be proc parse_type_list with parser
        proc add_child with enum_node, interfaces
    End If

    Note: Enum body
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer

    Note: Enum constants
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let is_rbrace be proc match with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer
        If is_rbrace is equal to 1:
            Break
        End If

        Let is_semicolon be proc match with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
        If is_semicolon is equal to 1:
            Break
        End If

        Let constant be proc parse_enum_constant with parser
        proc add_child with enum_node, constant

        Let is_comma be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer
        If is_comma is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    Note: Enum body declarations (optional)
    Set is_semicolon to proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
    If is_semicolon is equal to 1:
        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Set is_rbrace to proc match with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer
            If is_rbrace is equal to 1:
                Break
            End If

            Let member be proc parse_class_member with parser
            If member is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child with enum_node, member
            Otherwise:
                Break
            End If
        End While
    End If

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer

    Return enum_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: Annotations* Identifier ['(' ArgumentList ')'] [ClassBody]. The
optional argument list is for constants that invoke an enum constructor;
the optional class body provides per-constant method overrides (anonymous
subclass semantics).
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_enum_constant" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse enum constant

    Let constant_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_ENUM_CONSTANT

    Note: Annotations (optional)
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let is_at be proc match with parser, TOKEN_AT from Lexer
        If is_at is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If

        Let annotation be proc parse_annotation with parser
        proc add_child with constant_node, annotation
    End While

    Let name_token be proc current_token with parser
    Let constant_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with name_token, 8
    proc set_node_name with constant_node, constant_name

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer

    Note: Arguments (optional)
    Let is_lparen be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer
    If is_lparen is equal to 1:
        Let args be proc parse_argument_list with parser
        proc add_child with constant_node, args
        proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer
    End If

    Note: Class body (optional)
    Let is_lbrace be proc match with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer
    If is_lbrace is equal to 1:
        Let body be proc parse_class_body with parser
        proc add_child with constant_node, body
    End If

    Return constant_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: Modifiers '@' 'interface' Identifier '{' AnnotationMember* '}'.
The '@' must be followed directly by 'interface' — this caller has already
confirmed that via the dispatcher in parse_type_declaration.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_annotation_declaration" takes parser as Integer, modifiers as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse annotation type declaration

    Let annotation_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_ANNOTATION_DECLARATION

    If modifiers is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child with annotation_node, modifiers
    End If

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_AT from Lexer
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_INTERFACE from Lexer

    Let name_token be proc current_token with parser
    Let annotation_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with name_token, 8
    proc set_node_name with annotation_node, annotation_name

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer

    Note: Annotation body
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let is_rbrace be proc match with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer
        If is_rbrace is equal to 1:
            Break
        End If

        Let member be proc parse_annotation_member with parser
        If member is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child with annotation_node, member
        Otherwise:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer

    Return annotation_node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Modifiers and Annotations
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Consumes a sequence of access modifiers (public/private/protected),
non-access modifiers (static/final/abstract/synchronized/volatile/transient/
native/strictfp), and annotations into a single MODIFIER_LIST node.
Annotation handling is interleaved so '@Override public static' works the
same as 'public @Override static'. Stops at the first non-modifier token.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_modifiers" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse modifiers and annotations

    Let modifiers_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_MODIFIER_LIST

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser
        Let is_modifier be 0

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PUBLIC from Lexer:
            Set is_modifier to 1
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PRIVATE from Lexer:
            Set is_modifier to 1
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PROTECTED from Lexer:
            Set is_modifier to 1
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STATIC from Lexer:
            Set is_modifier to 1
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FINAL from Lexer:
            Set is_modifier to 1
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ABSTRACT from Lexer:
            Set is_modifier to 1
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SYNCHRONIZED from Lexer:
            Set is_modifier to 1
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to TOKEN_VOLATILE from Lexer:
            Set is_modifier to 1
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TRANSIENT from Lexer:
            Set is_modifier to 1
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to TOKEN_NATIVE from Lexer:
            Set is_modifier to 1
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STRICTFP from Lexer:
            Set is_modifier to 1
        Otherwise If token_type is equal to TOKEN_AT from Lexer:
            Note: An '@' is an annotation USE here only when it is not '@interface'
            Note: (the annotation-TYPE declaration keyword). Peek one token past
            Note: '@' via a save/restore lookahead: if 'interface' follows, this is
            Note: a type declaration, so stop collecting modifiers and leave the '@'
            Note: for parse_type_declaration. Otherwise consume the annotation use.
            Let at_lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
            Let at_scan_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 16
            Let at_line be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 24
            Let at_column be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 32
            Let at_current be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
            Let at_previous be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 16

            proc advance with parser  Note: Look at the token after '@'
            Let after_at be proc current_token_type with parser

            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 16, at_scan_pos
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 24, at_line
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 32, at_column
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, at_current
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, at_previous

            If after_at is equal to TOKEN_INTERFACE from Lexer:
                Break
            End If

            Let annotation be proc parse_annotation with parser
            proc add_child with modifiers_node, annotation
            Continue
        End If

        If is_modifier is equal to 1:
            Let token be proc current_token with parser
            Let modifier_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_IDENTIFIER
            proc set_node_token with modifier_node, token
            proc add_child with modifiers_node, modifier_node
            proc advance with parser
        Otherwise:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    Return modifiers_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a single annotation use site: '@' QualifiedName ['(' Args ')']. Args
may be either a single value expression or comma-separated name=value pairs;
parse_annotation_arguments treats both uniformly as expressions.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_annotation" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse annotation usage

    Let annotation_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_ANNOTATION

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_AT from Lexer

    Let name be proc parse_qualified_name with parser
    proc set_node_name with annotation_node, name

    Note: Annotation arguments (optional)
    Let is_lparen be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer
    If is_lparen is equal to 1:
        Note: Single value or name-value pairs
        Let args be proc parse_annotation_arguments with parser
        proc add_child with annotation_node, args
        proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer
    End If

    Return annotation_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Comma-separated expression list bounded by the closing right paren. Each
argument is parsed as a full expression — name-value pairs (e.g.,
key = "value") parse as assignment expressions and are decomposed by later
semantic passes.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_annotation_arguments" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse annotation arguments

    Let args_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_IDENTIFIER

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let is_rparen be proc match with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer
        If is_rparen is equal to 1:
            Break
        End If

        Let arg be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_child with args_node, arg

        Let is_comma be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer
        If is_comma is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    Return args_node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Class Member Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Dispatches on modifiers + first significant token to one of nested type,
constructor, method, or field. Constructor-vs-method ambiguity is resolved
by checking whether an identifier is immediately followed by '(' (the
identifier is the class name and we have no return type). Otherwise a type
reference is parsed first and the following identifier picks between method
and field by the LPAREN/SEMICOLON discriminator.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_class_member" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse class member (field, method, constructor, nested type)

    Let modifiers be proc parse_modifiers with parser

    Note: Method-level generic type parameters (e.g. public <R> R map(...)).
    Note: They appear after the modifiers and before the return type; parse and
    Note: discard the binding here so the subsequent return-type/name/'(' logic
    Note: sees the method signature proper. The type-parameter scope is recovered
    Note: by the semantic pass from the declaration's own generics where needed.
    Let has_type_params be proc match with parser, TOKEN_LT from Lexer
    If has_type_params is equal to 1:
        Let discarded_type_params be proc parse_type_parameters with parser
    End If

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    Note: Nested type declarations
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_class_declaration with parser, modifiers
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_INTERFACE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_interface_declaration with parser, modifiers
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ENUM from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_enum_declaration with parser, modifiers
    End If

    Note: Nested annotation-type declaration ('@interface'). The '@interface'
    Note: keyword pair is the only annotation-position form valid as a member
    Note: start (annotation USES were already absorbed by parse_modifiers). Peek
    Note: past '@' to confirm 'interface' before delegating.
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_AT from Lexer:
        Let at_lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
        Let at_scan_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 16
        Let at_line be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 24
        Let at_column be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 32
        Let at_current be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
        Let at_previous be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 16

        proc advance with parser
        Let after_at be proc current_token_type with parser

        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 16, at_scan_pos
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 24, at_line
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with at_lexer, 32, at_column
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, at_current
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, at_previous

        If after_at is equal to TOKEN_INTERFACE from Lexer:
            Return proc parse_annotation_declaration with parser, modifiers
        End If
    End If

    Note: Constructor, method, or field. A member begins with either a primitive
    Note: type keyword or an identifier that opens a reference type. In every case
    Note: we parse a COMPLETE type reference first - this is what lets generic
    Note: (Map<String, List<Integer>>), qualified (java.util.List), and array
    Note: (String[]) member types be read correctly rather than being truncated by
    Note: a one-token peek. The disambiguation is then purely on what follows the
    Note: type: a '(' means the "type" was actually a CONSTRUCTOR name (constructors
    Note: have no return type), so the member name is that type's simple name and the
    Note: parameter list follows immediately; an identifier means a normal
    Note: method/return-type or field/field-type declaration, disambiguated by
    Note: whether a '(' follows the member name.
    Let type_ref be proc parse_type_reference with parser

    Let after_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    If after_type is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        Note: Constructor: the parsed "type" is the constructor (class) name. Its
        Note: simple name lives in the type reference node's name slot (offset 16).
        Let ctor_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_ref, 16
        Return proc parse_constructor_declaration with parser, modifiers, ctor_name
    End If

    Let name_token be proc current_token with parser
    Let member_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with name_token, 8

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer

    Let next_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    If next_type is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        Note: Method
        Return proc parse_method_declaration_with_type with parser, modifiers, type_ref, member_name
    Otherwise:
        Note: Field
        Return proc parse_field_declaration_with_type with parser, modifiers, type_ref, member_name
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Interface members are abstract methods, default methods (Java 8+), constant
fields, or nested types — interfaces have no constructors. After modifiers
and a type reference, the LPAREN/SEMICOLON discriminator picks
method-vs-field.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_interface_member" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse interface member (method, field, nested type)

    Let modifiers be proc parse_modifiers with parser

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    Note: Nested type declarations
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_class_declaration with parser, modifiers
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_INTERFACE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_interface_declaration with parser, modifiers
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ENUM from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_enum_declaration with parser, modifiers
    End If

    Note: Method or constant field
    Let type_ref be proc parse_type_reference with parser

    Let name_token be proc current_token with parser
    Let member_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with name_token, 8

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer

    Let next_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    If next_type is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        Note: Method
        Return proc parse_method_declaration_with_type with parser, modifiers, type_ref, member_name
    Otherwise:
        Note: Constant field
        Return proc parse_field_declaration_with_type with parser, modifiers, type_ref, member_name
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Annotation element grammar: Type Identifier '(' ')' ['default' Expression]
';'. The mandatory empty parameter list distinguishes annotation elements
from regular interface members. Default values are AST children if present.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_annotation_member" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse annotation member (annotation element)

    Let modifiers be proc parse_modifiers with parser

    Let type_ref be proc parse_type_reference with parser

    Let name_token be proc current_token with parser
    Let member_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with name_token, 8

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

    Let member_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_METHOD_DECLARATION
    proc set_node_name with member_node, member_name

    If modifiers is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child with member_node, modifiers
    End If

    proc add_child with member_node, type_ref

    Note: Default value (optional)
    Let is_default be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_DEFAULT from Lexer
    If is_default is equal to 1:
        Let default_value be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_child with member_node, default_value
    End If

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

    Return member_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Constructors have no return type. Caller has already consumed the
constructor identifier (the class name). Grammar: Modifiers Name '('
ParameterList ')' ['throws' TypeList] Block.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_constructor_declaration" takes parser as Integer, modifiers as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse constructor declaration

    Let constructor_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_CONSTRUCTOR_DECLARATION
    proc set_node_name with constructor_node, name

    If modifiers is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child with constructor_node, modifiers
    End If

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer

    Let params be proc parse_parameter_list with parser
    proc add_child with constructor_node, params

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

    Note: Throws clause (optional)
    Let is_throws be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_THROWS from Lexer
    If is_throws is equal to 1:
        Let exceptions be proc parse_type_list with parser
        proc add_child with constructor_node, exceptions
    End If

    Note: Constructor body
    Let body be proc parse_block with parser
    proc add_child with constructor_node, body

    Return constructor_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Continuation entry point — caller has already parsed the return type and
identifier. Grammar: '(' ParameterList ')' ['throws' TypeList] (Block | ';').
A semicolon (no body) marks an abstract or interface method.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_method_declaration_with_type" takes parser as Integer, modifiers as Integer, return_type as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse method declaration with known type

    Let method_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_METHOD_DECLARATION
    proc set_node_name with method_node, name

    If modifiers is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child with method_node, modifiers
    End If

    proc add_child with method_node, return_type

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer

    Let params be proc parse_parameter_list with parser
    proc add_child with method_node, params

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

    Note: Throws clause (optional)
    Let is_throws be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_THROWS from Lexer
    If is_throws is equal to 1:
        Let exceptions be proc parse_type_list with parser
        proc add_child with method_node, exceptions
    End If

    Note: Method body or semicolon (abstract/interface method)
    Let is_semicolon be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
    If is_semicolon is equal to 0:
        Let body be proc parse_block with parser
        proc add_child with method_node, body
    End If

    Return method_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Continuation entry point — caller has already parsed the type and the field
name. Handles trailing C-style array dimensions on the field name (int x[];
form), an optional '= initializer', and the terminating semicolon.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_field_declaration_with_type" takes parser as Integer, modifiers as Integer, field_type as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse field declaration with known type

    Let field_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_FIELD_DECLARATION
    proc set_node_name with field_node, name

    If modifiers is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child with field_node, modifiers
    End If

    proc add_child with field_node, field_type

    Note: Array dimensions (optional)
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let is_lbracket be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer
        If is_lbracket is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
        proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer
    End While

    Note: Initializer (optional)
    Let is_assign be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer
    If is_assign is equal to 1:
        Let initializer be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_child with field_node, initializer
    End If

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

    Return field_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses zero or more comma-separated parameters between the parens. Empty
list short-circuits on immediate RPAREN. The closing paren itself is not
consumed here — caller validates the matching ')'.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_parameter_list" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse method parameter list

    Let params_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_IDENTIFIER

    Let is_rparen be proc match with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer
    If is_rparen is equal to 1:
        Return params_node
    End If

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let param be proc parse_parameter with parser
        proc add_child with params_node, param

        Let is_comma be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer
        If is_comma is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    Return params_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: Modifiers Type ['...'] Identifier. The '...' varargs marker is
stored in the node's value slot (1 = varargs). Modifiers here may include
'final' and annotations (e.g., @Nullable).
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_parameter" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse method parameter

    Let param_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_PARAMETER

    Note: Modifiers (final, annotations)
    Let modifiers be proc parse_modifiers with parser
    If modifiers is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child with param_node, modifiers
    End If

    Let param_type be proc parse_type_reference with parser
    proc add_child with param_node, param_type

    Note: Varargs (...)
    Let is_ellipsis be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_ELLIPSIS from Lexer
    If is_ellipsis is equal to 1:
        proc set_node_value with param_node, 1  Note: Mark as varargs
    End If

    Let name_token be proc current_token with parser
    Let param_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with name_token, 8
    proc set_node_name with param_node, param_name

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer

    Return param_node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Type Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Universal type-reference parser. Recognizes all eight Java primitives plus
void (no array on void), or falls through to a qualified-name reference
type with optional generic arguments. Primitive parses always continue into
parse_array_dimensions to attach trailing []s. The token attached to
primitive nodes preserves the spelling for downstream selectors.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_type_reference" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse type reference (primitive, reference, array, generic)

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    Note: Primitive types
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_BOOLEAN_TYPE from Lexer:
        Let type_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_TYPE_REFERENCE
        Let token be proc current_token with parser
        proc set_node_token with type_node, token
        proc advance with parser
        Return proc parse_array_dimensions with parser, type_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_BYTE from Lexer:
        Set type_node to proc create_ast_node with AST_TYPE_REFERENCE
        Set token to proc current_token with parser
        proc set_node_token with type_node, token
        proc advance with parser
        Return proc parse_array_dimensions with parser, type_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SHORT from Lexer:
        Set type_node to proc create_ast_node with AST_TYPE_REFERENCE
        Set token to proc current_token with parser
        proc set_node_token with type_node, token
        proc advance with parser
        Return proc parse_array_dimensions with parser, type_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_INT_TYPE from Lexer:
        Set type_node to proc create_ast_node with AST_TYPE_REFERENCE
        Set token to proc current_token with parser
        proc set_node_token with type_node, token
        proc advance with parser
        Return proc parse_array_dimensions with parser, type_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LONG_TYPE from Lexer:
        Set type_node to proc create_ast_node with AST_TYPE_REFERENCE
        Set token to proc current_token with parser
        proc set_node_token with type_node, token
        proc advance with parser
        Return proc parse_array_dimensions with parser, type_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FLOAT_TYPE from Lexer:
        Set type_node to proc create_ast_node with AST_TYPE_REFERENCE
        Set token to proc current_token with parser
        proc set_node_token with type_node, token
        proc advance with parser
        Return proc parse_array_dimensions with parser, type_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_DOUBLE_TYPE from Lexer:
        Set type_node to proc create_ast_node with AST_TYPE_REFERENCE
        Set token to proc current_token with parser
        proc set_node_token with type_node, token
        proc advance with parser
        Return proc parse_array_dimensions with parser, type_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CHAR_TYPE from Lexer:
        Set type_node to proc create_ast_node with AST_TYPE_REFERENCE
        Set token to proc current_token with parser
        proc set_node_token with type_node, token
        proc advance with parser
        Return proc parse_array_dimensions with parser, type_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_VOID from Lexer:
        Set type_node to proc create_ast_node with AST_TYPE_REFERENCE
        Set token to proc current_token with parser
        proc set_node_token with type_node, token
        proc advance with parser
        Return type_node
    End If

    Note: Reference type (qualified name with optional generics)
    Let qualified_name be proc parse_qualified_name with parser

    Set type_node to proc create_ast_node with AST_TYPE_REFERENCE
    proc set_node_name with type_node, qualified_name

    Note: Generic type arguments (optional)
    Let is_lt be proc match with parser, TOKEN_LT from Lexer
    If is_lt is equal to 1:
        Let type_args be proc parse_type_arguments with parser
        proc add_child with type_node, type_args
    End If

    Return proc parse_array_dimensions with parser, type_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Consumes a run of '[]' suffixes after a type or variable name. If at least
one pair is seen, wraps base_type in an ARRAY_TYPE node; otherwise returns
base_type unchanged so non-array references don't acquire an extra wrapper.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_array_dimensions" takes parser as Integer, base_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse array dimensions []

    Let has_brackets be 0

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let is_lbracket be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer
        If is_lbracket is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If

        proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer
        Set has_brackets to 1
    End While

    If has_brackets is equal to 1:
        Let array_type be proc create_ast_node with AST_ARRAY_TYPE
        proc add_child with array_type, base_type
        Return array_type
    End If

    Return base_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: '<' TypeParameter (',' TypeParameter)* '>'. Used for generic
class/interface/method declarations. Each parameter is itself parsed with
parse_type_parameter and may carry extends bounds.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_type_parameters" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse generic type parameters <T, U extends Base>

    Let type_params_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_TYPE_PARAMETER

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LT from Lexer

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let param be proc parse_type_parameter with parser
        proc add_child with type_params_node, param

        Let is_comma be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer
        If is_comma is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    proc expect_generic_close with parser

    Return type_params_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: Identifier ['extends' TypeBound]. Identifier becomes the parameter
name; the optional bounds list (one type or intersection like
'T extends A & B') becomes a child.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_type_parameter" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse single type parameter (T extends Base bitwise and Interface)

    Let param_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_TYPE_PARAMETER

    Let name_token be proc current_token with parser
    Let param_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with name_token, 8
    proc set_node_name with param_node, param_name

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer

    Note: Type bounds (extends)
    Let is_extends be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_EXTENDS from Lexer
    If is_extends is equal to 1:
        Let bounds be proc parse_type_bound_list with parser
        proc add_child with param_node, bounds
    End If

    Return param_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses one or more bound types separated by '&' (BITAND). The '&' here is
syntactically the bitwise-AND token reused as the intersection-type
separator per JLS. The first bound may be a class; subsequent bounds must
be interfaces, but that constraint is enforced semantically, not here.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_type_bound_list" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse type bound list (Base bitwise and Interface1 bitwise and Interface2)

    Let bounds_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_TYPE_BOUND

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let bound_type be proc parse_type_reference with parser
        proc add_child with bounds_node, bound_type

        Let is_and be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_BITAND from Lexer
        If is_and is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    Return bounds_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Consumes exactly ONE closing generic angle bracket. The lexer is greedy and
merges adjacent '>' characters into the shift tokens '>>' (TOKEN_RSHIFT) and
'>>>' (TOKEN_URSHIFT), and '>=' / '>>=' / '>>>=' when an '=' follows - which
is correct for shift expressions but wrong inside nested generics such as
Map<String, List<Integer>> where the trailing '>>' actually closes two
generic scopes. This helper closes one level: a plain '>' is consumed by
advancing; a multi-'>' token is split in place by rewriting its token type
(at offset 0) to the token representing the remaining characters, WITHOUT
advancing, so the next enclosing generic scope consumes the rest. This is the
standard Java-parser angle-bracket splitting technique and lets arbitrarily
deep nesting (List<Map<K, List<V>>>) close correctly.
@End Reasoning
Process called "expect_generic_close" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Let token be proc current_token with parser
    If token is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let token_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with token, 0

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_GT from Lexer:
        proc advance with parser
        Return 1
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RSHIFT from Lexer:
        Note: '>>' closes one level here; rewrite to a single '>' for the parent.
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with token, 0, TOKEN_GT from Lexer
        Return 1
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_URSHIFT from Lexer:
        Note: '>>>' closes one level here; rewrite to '>>' for the parent.
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with token, 0, TOKEN_RSHIFT from Lexer
        Return 1
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_GE from Lexer:
        Note: '>=' in type-close position closes one '>' and leaves '='.
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with token, 0, TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer
        Return 1
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RSHIFTASSIGN from Lexer:
        Note: '>>=' closes one '>' and leaves '>='.
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with token, 0, TOKEN_GE from Lexer
        Return 1
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_URSHIFTASSIGN from Lexer:
        Note: '>>>=' closes one '>' and leaves '>>='.
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with token, 0, TOKEN_RSHIFTASSIGN from Lexer
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: '<' TypeArgument (',' TypeArgument)* '>'. Used at type-reference
use sites (e.g., List<String>). Each argument may be a wildcard or a regular
type reference.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_type_arguments" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse generic type arguments <String, Integer>

    Let type_args_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_GENERIC_TYPE

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LT from Lexer

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let arg be proc parse_type_argument with parser
        proc add_child with type_args_node, arg

        Let is_comma be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer
        If is_comma is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    proc expect_generic_close with parser

    Return type_args_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
A type argument is either a wildcard ('?' with optional extends/super
bound) or a regular type reference. The leading '?' is the discriminator.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_type_argument" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse single type argument (Type or ? extends Type or ? super Type)

    Let is_question be proc match with parser, TOKEN_QUESTION from Lexer
    If is_question is equal to 1:
        Return proc parse_wildcard_type with parser
    End If

    Return proc parse_type_reference with parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: '?' [('extends' | 'super') Type]. The variance is encoded in the
value slot: 0 = unbounded '?', 1 = extends, 2 = super. The bound type, if
any, is the single child.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_wildcard_type" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse wildcard type (? extends Type or ? super Type)

    Let wildcard_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_WILDCARD_TYPE

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_QUESTION from Lexer

    Let is_extends be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_EXTENDS from Lexer
    If is_extends is equal to 1:
        proc set_node_value with wildcard_node, 1  Note: extends bound
        Let bound be proc parse_type_reference with parser
        proc add_child with wildcard_node, bound
        Return wildcard_node
    End If

    Let is_super be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_SUPER from Lexer
    If is_super is equal to 1:
        proc set_node_value with wildcard_node, 2  Note: super bound
        Set bound to proc parse_type_reference with parser
        proc add_child with wildcard_node, bound
        Return wildcard_node
    End If

    Return wildcard_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Comma-separated type references with no surrounding delimiters. Used for
implements clauses, multi-extends on interfaces, throws clauses, and so on.
The caller is responsible for any trailing token (semicolon, brace, etc.).
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_type_list" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse comma-separated type list

    Let list_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_IDENTIFIER

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let type_ref be proc parse_type_reference with parser
        proc add_child with list_node, type_ref

        Let is_comma be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer
        If is_comma is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    Return list_node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Statement Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Grammar: '{' Statement* '}'. Iterates parse_statement until RBRACE or until
a statement parse fails to make progress (then we exit and let the closing
expect catch a missing brace).
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_block" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse block statement

    Let block_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_BLOCK

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let is_rbrace be proc match with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer
        If is_rbrace is equal to 1:
            Break
        End If

        Let stmt be proc parse_statement with parser
        If stmt is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child with block_node, stmt
        Otherwise:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer

    Return block_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Statement dispatcher: a leading keyword (if/while/for/return/throw/try/
switch/break/continue) picks a specialized production; LBRACE recurses into
a nested block; lone SEMICOLON is an empty statement (returns a placeholder
node); anything else falls through to expression-or-declaration.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse statement

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IF from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_if_statement with parser
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_WHILE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_while_statement with parser
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_DO from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_do_while_statement with parser
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FOR from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_for_statement with parser
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RETURN from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_return_statement with parser
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_THROW from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_throw_statement with parser
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TRY from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_try_statement with parser
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SWITCH from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_switch_statement with parser
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_BREAK from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_break_statement with parser
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CONTINUE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_continue_statement with parser
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_block with parser
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
        proc advance with parser
        Return proc create_ast_node with AST_IDENTIFIER  Note: Empty statement
    End If

    Note: Expression statement or variable declaration
    Return proc parse_expression_or_declaration with parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: 'if' '(' Expression ')' Statement ['else' Statement]. Dangling-else
is resolved by the natural recursive descent: the else binds to the
innermost still-open if because we parse it eagerly after the then-branch.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_if_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse if statement

    Let if_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_IF_STATEMENT

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IF from Lexer
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer

    Let condition be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc add_child with if_node, condition

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

    Let then_stmt be proc parse_statement with parser
    proc add_child with if_node, then_stmt

    Note: Else clause (optional)
    Let is_else be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_ELSE from Lexer
    If is_else is equal to 1:
        Let else_stmt be proc parse_statement with parser
        proc add_child with if_node, else_stmt
    End If

    Return if_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: 'while' '(' Expression ')' Statement. The condition is the first
child, the body is the second; downstream code can rely on that ordering.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_while_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse while statement

    Let while_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_WHILE_STATEMENT

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_WHILE from Lexer
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer

    Let condition be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc add_child with while_node, condition

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

    Let body be proc parse_statement with parser
    proc add_child with while_node, body

    Return while_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: 'do' Statement 'while' '(' Expression ')' ';'. The body executes at
least once before the condition is tested. The body is stored as the first
child and the condition as the second, mirroring the while-statement ordering
inverted-evaluation aside, so HIR consumers read children[0] = body and
children[1] = condition.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_do_while_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse do-while statement

    Let do_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_DO_WHILE_STATEMENT

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_DO from Lexer

    Let body be proc parse_statement with parser
    proc add_child with do_node, body

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_WHILE from Lexer
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer

    Let condition be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc add_child with do_node, condition

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

    Return do_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Top of the for-statement parse. Distinguishes traditional C-style for from
the enhanced for-each by peeking with check_enhanced_for and routing to the
appropriate body. The leading 'for' '(' is consumed here so both branches
share that prefix.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_for_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse for statement (traditional or enhanced for-each)

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_FOR from Lexer
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer

    Note: Check for enhanced for (for (Type var : collection))
    Note: This requires lookahead to distinguish from traditional for
    Let is_enhanced be proc check_enhanced_for with parser

    If is_enhanced is equal to 1:
        Return proc parse_enhanced_for with parser
    End If

    Return proc parse_traditional_for with parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Lookahead-only predicate: speculatively scans Type Identifier ':' without
committing. Because the lexer scans on demand (no pre-tokenized buffer), a
true rewind must restore the lexer scan position (offset 16) and line/column
(offsets 24/32) together with the parser's current and previous token slots.
We reuse the real parse_type_reference so the lookahead recognizes exactly
the same type grammar the committed parse would (primitives, qualified
names, generics, array dimensions). Returns 1 when a colon follows the type
and binding identifier (enhanced for-each), 0 otherwise.
@End Reasoning
Process called "check_enhanced_for" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Enhanced for has pattern: Type identifier : expression
    Note: Traditional for has pattern: init; condition; increment

    Note: Save full lexer scan state and parser token slots for backtracking.
    Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
    Let saved_scan_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16
    Let saved_line be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 24
    Let saved_column be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 32
    Let saved_current be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
    Let saved_previous be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 16

    Note: A binding may be preceded by 'final' and/or annotations.
    Let pre_type be proc current_token_type with parser
    While pre_type is equal to TOKEN_FINAL from Lexer:
        proc advance with parser
        Set pre_type to proc current_token_type with parser
    End While
    While pre_type is equal to TOKEN_AT from Lexer:
        proc advance with parser
        Set pre_type to proc current_token_type with parser
        If pre_type is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
            proc advance with parser
            Set pre_type to proc current_token_type with parser
        End If
    End While

    Note: Speculatively consume a full type reference using the real grammar.
    Let type_node be proc parse_type_reference with parser

    Let result be 0
    If type_node is not equal to 0:
        Let after_type be proc current_token_type with parser
        If after_type is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
            proc advance with parser
            Let after_ident be proc current_token_type with parser
            If after_ident is equal to TOKEN_COLON from Lexer:
                Set result to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Restore the saved lexer and parser state regardless of outcome.
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16, saved_scan_pos
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 24, saved_line
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 32, saved_column
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, saved_current
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, saved_previous

    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: for '(' [init] ';' [cond] ';' [update] ')' Statement. Each of the
three sections is optional and may be empty (omission detected by an
immediate semicolon or RPAREN). The expression-or-declaration parser is
used for the init so 'int i = 0' and 'i = 0' both work.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_traditional_for" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse traditional for statement

    Let for_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_FOR_STATEMENT

    Note: Initializer (optional)
    Let is_semicolon be proc match with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
    If is_semicolon is equal to 0:
        Let init be proc parse_expression_or_declaration with parser
        proc add_child with for_node, init
    Otherwise:
        proc advance with parser
    End If

    Note: Condition (optional)
    Set is_semicolon to proc match with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
    If is_semicolon is equal to 0:
        Let condition be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_child with for_node, condition
    End If

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

    Note: Update (optional)
    Let is_rparen be proc match with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer
    If is_rparen is equal to 0:
        Let update be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_child with for_node, update
    End If

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

    Let body be proc parse_statement with parser
    proc add_child with for_node, body

    Return for_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: for '(' Type Identifier ':' Expression ')' Statement. The element
type and name describe the per-iteration variable; the expression is the
Iterable / array. Element name is stored on the node, collection and body
are children.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_enhanced_for" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse enhanced for statement (for-each)

    Let for_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_ENHANCED_FOR

    Note: Loop-variable type is the first child; its name is stored on the node.
    Let element_type be proc parse_type_reference with parser
    proc add_child with for_node, element_type

    Let name_token be proc current_token with parser
    Let element_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with name_token, 8
    proc set_node_name with for_node, element_name

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_COLON from Lexer

    Let collection be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc add_child with for_node, collection

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

    Let body be proc parse_statement with parser
    proc add_child with for_node, body

    Return for_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: 'return' [Expression] ';'. Empty return (no expression) is detected
by an immediate semicolon; in that case the return node has no children.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_return_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse return statement

    Let return_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_RETURN_STATEMENT

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RETURN from Lexer

    Let is_semicolon be proc match with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
    If is_semicolon is equal to 0:
        Let value be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_child with return_node, value
    End If

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

    Return return_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: 'throw' Expression ';'. Java requires the operand (no bare throw),
so we always parse an expression with no optionality check.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_throw_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse throw statement

    Let throw_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_THROW_STATEMENT

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_THROW from Lexer

    Let exception be proc parse_expression with parser
    proc add_child with throw_node, exception

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

    Return throw_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: 'try' ['(' Resources ')'] Block Catch* ['finally' Block]. Handles
try, try-with-resources (Java 7+), multi-catch chains, and the optional
finally. Java requires at least one catch or finally; this parser does not
enforce that — semantic analysis catches missing handlers.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_try_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse try statement (with optional resources, catch, finally)

    Let try_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_TRY_STATEMENT

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_TRY from Lexer

    Note: Try-with-resources (optional)
    Let is_lparen be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer
    If is_lparen is equal to 1:
        Let resources be proc parse_resource_list with parser
        proc add_child with try_node, resources
        proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer
    End If

    Note: Try block
    Let try_block be proc parse_block with parser
    proc add_child with try_node, try_block

    Note: Catch clauses (zero or more)
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let is_catch be proc match with parser, TOKEN_CATCH from Lexer
        If is_catch is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If

        Let catch_clause be proc parse_catch_clause with parser
        proc add_child with try_node, catch_clause
    End While

    Note: Finally block (optional)
    Let is_finally be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_FINALLY from Lexer
    If is_finally is equal to 1:
        Let finally_block be proc parse_block with parser
        proc add_child with try_node, finally_block
    End If

    Return try_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: 'catch' '(' Type Identifier ')' Block. Multi-catch (Type1 | Type2)
is not split into separate clauses here; that lives in parse_type_reference
or upstream of it depending on grammar revision.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_catch_clause" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse catch clause

    Let catch_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_CATCH_CLAUSE

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_CATCH from Lexer
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer

    Let exception_type be proc parse_type_reference with parser
    proc add_child with catch_node, exception_type

    Let name_token be proc current_token with parser
    Let exception_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with name_token, 8
    proc set_node_name with catch_node, exception_name

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer

    Let catch_block be proc parse_block with parser
    proc add_child with catch_node, catch_block

    Return catch_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Try-with-resources resource list: one or more resource specifications
separated by ';'. Trailing semicolons are tolerated by terminating on
'no semicolon' detection.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_resource_list" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse resource list for try-with-resources

    Let resources_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_IDENTIFIER

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let resource be proc parse_resource_specification with parser
        proc add_child with resources_node, resource

        Let is_semicolon be proc match_and_advance with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
        If is_semicolon is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If

        Let is_rparen be proc match with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer
        If is_rparen is equal to 1:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    Return resources_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Grammar: Type Identifier '=' Expression. Reuses the variable-declaration
node shape so the catch-finally machinery can dispose() each resource the
same way ordinary locals are scoped.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_resource_specification" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse single resource specification

    Let resource_type be proc parse_type_reference with parser

    Let name_token be proc current_token with parser
    Let resource_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with name_token, 8

    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer
    proc expect with parser, TOKEN_ASSIGN from Lexer

    Let initializer be proc parse_expression with parser

    Let resource_node be proc create_ast_node with AST_VARIABLE_DECLARATION
    proc set_node_name with resource_node, resource_name
    proc add_child with resource_node, resource_type
