The body of a switch arrow label ('case X ->' / 'default ->') is exactly one
of: a brace block ({ ... }), or a single statement - an expression statement
(case 1 -> 10;), a throw statement (case 2 -> throw e;), or a yield.
A block is parsed via parse_block; everything else is delegated to
parse_statement, which already consumes its own terminating ';' and dispatches
throw/expression forms. Exactly one body node is produced, which the emitter
prints after ' -> '.
