    Note: form ('case X -> expr;' or 'case X -> { ... }') which has exactly one
    Note: body with no fall-through. The form is recorded in the node value slot
    Note: (0 = classic case, 2 = arrow case) so the emitter reproduces the right
    Note: syntax; the default clause uses 1 / 3 for the same distinction.

