    Note: Use lookahead to distinguish between expression and declaration
    Note: Variable declaration patterns: Type identifier [= initializer];
    Note: Expression patterns: identifier.method(), identifier[index], etc.

    Note: Save FULL lexer + parser state for backtracking. The lexer scans on
    Note: demand (no token buffer), so a rewind must restore the lexer scan
    Note: position (offset 16) and line/column (24/32) along with the parser's
    Note: current and previous token slots; restoring the parser slots alone
    Note: would leave the lexer advanced and corrupt the subsequent re-parse.
